cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
1) cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design of a secure plausibly deniable system for mobile devices against multi-snapshot adversaries. 
2) cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a new design for integrating PDE into the flash translation layer (FTL) of mobile devices. 
3) cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of flash memory as the underlying storage medium for the PDE system. 
4) cs.OS (Operating Systems) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of full disk encryption in mobile operating systems and proposes a new design for integrating PDE into the FTL of mobile devices. 
5) cs.DB (Databases) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the storage and management of sensitive data on mobile devices.
